HEADWORD: V moth
<hw>V" moth`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A common gray
European moth (<spn>Halia vauaria</spn>) having a
<universbold>V</universbold>-shaped spot of dark brown on each of the
fore wings.</def>⟦br⟧
